de.tuhh.diss.harborstorage.sim

Interface HighBayStorage


  • public interface HighBayStorage
    This interfaces abstracts the main functionality of a harbor storage management system. It provides methods to store and retrieve packets to/from the harbor storage.
    Author:
    Weigel / Venzke

    • Method Detail

      • storePacket

        int storePacket(int width,
                int height,
                int depth,
                java.lang.String description,
                int weight)
         throws StorageException
        This method shall store a packet with the given dimensions in one of the smallest possible slots of the storage area. The created packet shall be identifiable by a unique number. Note that packets fit into a slot of the high rack if all dimensions are smaller or are equal than those of the slot. Packets are NOT supposed to be flipped over or rotated to fit a certain slot! E.g. a packet with the size of 2x4x2 (WIDTHxHEIGHTxDEPTH) will neither fit into a slot of size 4x2x2 nor into one of the size 2x2x4, but will only fit into a slot of size 2x4x2.
        Parameters:
        width - the size of the packet in x-direction
        height - the size of the packet in y-direction
        depth - the size of the packet in z-direction
        description - a short textual description of the content
        weight - the weight of the packet
        Returns:
        The identifier of the stored generated packet.
        Throws:
        StorageException - if the packet cannot be stored (because no slot is available) or the packet could not be created

      • retrievePacket

        void retrievePacket(java.lang.String description)
             throws StorageException
        This method shall remove the packet with the given description from the storage. After this method has been executed, no trace of the packet shall remain within the harbor storage.
        Parameters:
        description - the description of the packet to be retrieved from the harbor storage
        Throws:
        StorageException - if the packet could not be found within the system
